# Week 1 - DevOps & Docker Basics

## What is DevOps?
DevOps is a practice that combines Development and Operations to improve collaboration and automate workflows.

## Virtualization
- Partition physical server into multiple virtual machines
- Uses Hypervisor
- Advantages:
  - Better resource utilization
  - Cost saving
  - Security

## Drawbacks
- Heavy resource usage
- Slow boot time
- Complex management

## Containerization
- Lightweight alternative to virtualization
- Shares host OS
- Fast startup
- Efficient resource usage

## Need of Containers
- Microservices architecture
- Portability
- Scalability
